article.headline: Mazzante scores 26 as Nittany Lions win by 31
article.linkText: Mazzante leads way to easy victory for No. 14 Penn State
article.story:
MADISON, Wis. (AP) -- Kelly Mazzante scored 26 points, and Penn State (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today; No. 15 Associated Press) never trailed en route to an 86-55 victory Thursday
night over Wisconsin in the Big Ten opener for both.

	   Reserve Jennifer Brenden added a career-high 15 points, all in
the first half, for Penn State (10-2). The Nittany Lions also got
12 points from Ashli Schwab and 11 apiece from Tanisha Wright and
Jessica Brungo while beating the Badgers for the seventh time in
their last eight meetings.

	   Lello Gebisa set career highs with 23 points and 11 rebounds to
lead Wisconsin (2-8), off to its worst start since the 1987-88
season.

	   Wisconsin kept the score close early until Brenden got hot from
behind the 3-point line to help Penn State pull away. She hit three
3-pointers to spark an 11-2 run that gave Penn State a 28-15 lead
with less than 10 minutes remaining in the first half.

	   Brenden entered the game with just five career 3-pointers. But
she had a breakthrough performance against Wisconsin, going 5-for-5
from behind the arc in the first half as Penn State took a 50-25
lead into the break.

	   Wisconsin never got closer than 19 points the rest of the way.
Mazzante, who made nine 3-pointers and scored 34 points against
Wisconsin in the conference tournament semifinals last season, made
just one from beyond the arc this time. But she was 9-for-11 from
the free-throw line.

	   Led by Brenden, Penn State was 8-for-15 from 3-point range in
the first half.
